com.tinkerpop.rexster.gremlin.converter

Interface ResultConverter<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type to convert Gremlin output to.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConsoleResultConverter, JSONResultConverter, MsgPackResultConverter

    public interface ResultConverter<T>
    A ResultConverter converts output from Gremlin to some other format.

    An example is the ConsoleResultConverter which takes Gremlin output and converts it to a list of Strings for display in the Console.

    Author:
    Stephen Mallette (http://stephen.genoprime.com)

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      T convert(Object result)
      Converts the result to a sensible format given the implementation.

    • Method Detail

      • convert

        T convert(Object result)
          throws Exception
        Converts the result to a sensible format given the implementation.

        Gremlin can send back many different kinds of output as a result. That output is the value passed to this method to be processed and converted to some other type. A result may be an Iterator, Vertex, Edge, numeric, string, etc. Implementation is not trivial.

        Throws:
        Exception
